title: Gionee F5 with 5.3-inch display, 4GB RAM and 4,000mAh battery launched
text:
Gionee F5 with 5.3-inch display, 4GB RAM and 4,000mAh battery launched Gionee F5 with 5.3-inch display, 4GB RAM and 4,000mAh battery launched By - February 7, 2017 “The F5 is a mid-range phablet with 32GB of storage, 13MP/8MP cameras and an all-metal body” 
Soon after launching the Steel 2 with a 4,000mAh battery last month, Gionee has launched yet another battery-centric smartphone. Dubbed the Gionee F5, the new phone has been released in the brand’s home market of China. Similar to the Steel 2, the F5 also features a 4,000mAh battery. The F5 also features a metal unibody design and a fingerprint sensor that’s integrated into its home button. 
As far as the other specs go, the Gionee F5 features a 5.3-inch HD IPS display, and boots Android 6.0 Marshmallow. The phone utilises a 64-bit octa-core MediaTek MT6750 processor, mated to 4GB of RAM. The storage capacity on board is 32GB, further expandable up to 128GB by inserting a microSD card. 
The camera department on the Gionee F5 includes a 13-megapixel primary shooter with an LED flash, autofocus and full HD recording, and an 8-megapixel selfie snapper. In terms of connectivity, the phone offers 4G LTE, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth and GPS. 
The Gionee F5 has been priced at RMB 1,799, roughly Rs 17,600. The phone is currently available to buy in China only.
